      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Quality settings + low-VRAM tweaks\n\nDefaults below target a **higher-fidelity safe** combo verified on an RTX 5090: 1024_cascade + 16/16/16 sampling steps + 65k tokens + 300k decimation + 4096 texture. Wall time: ~3-4 min once the pipeline is warm; ~7-10 min on the first run after a ComfyUI restart (cold-load).\n\nIf you OOM on a 12-16 GB card, edit the **Pixal3DImageToMesh** widgets in this order until it fits:\n\n1. **max_num_tokens**: 65536 -> **24576** (smaller HR activation budget)\n2. **ss / shape / tex sampling_steps**: 16 -> **8** each\n3. **decimation_target**: 300000 -> **100000** (lighter mesh post-proc)\n4. **texture_size**: 4096 -> **1024**\n5. **low_vram**: false -> **true** (CPU offload between stages; ~2x wall time)\n\nCards with 24 GB+ should **stay on 1024_cascade**. The 1536_cascade pipeline overshoots VRAM once ComfyUI Desktop reserves its 16 GB cast buffer - see the README \"Memory + performance\" table."
      ],
      "title": "Low-VRAM tweaks (read first)",
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
